This paper deals with inverse problems in imaging, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses regularization techniques, which could place it under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of denoisers for regularization also suggests that it could belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image synthesis, which could place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
